<div class="research-left">

<div class="field-field_thumbnail field-label-hidden">
            <div>  <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/partner_logo/public/2020-10/logo.png?itok=SqE7OdnK" width="158" height="56" alt="" typeof="foaf:Image" />


</div>
      </div>

<h2><span>Making the Grade? How state public school standards address climate change</span>
</h2>
<a href="https://ncse.ngo/files/MakingTheGrade_Final_10.8.2020.pdf">
<div class="field-field_type_of_study field-label-hidden">
            <div>Read the study</div>
      </div>
</a>
<div class="cover"><a href="https://ncse.ngo/files/MakingTheGrade_Final_10.8.2020.pdf"></a></div>
</div>
<div class="research-right">
    
<div class="field-field_topics field-label-hidden">
      <div>
              <div>Climate change</div>
          </div>
  </div>

<div class="field-field_year field-label-hidden">
            <div>2020</div>
      </div>


<div class="field-field_body">

          <article><p><em><strong><span>Making the Grade? How State Public School Standards Address Climate Change </span></strong></em><span>provides an analysis of every state's science standards when it comes to climate change. Developed by NCSE and the Texas Freedom Network Education Fund, the report has a <a href="https://climategrades.org/">companion website</a> with an interactive map.</span></p></article>
    
</div>


