<div class="research-left">

<div class="field-field_thumbnail field-label-hidden">
            <div>  <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/partner_logo/public/2019-08/logo.png?itok=UMSQvqG-" width="158" height="56" alt="" typeof="foaf:Image" />


</div>
      </div>

<h2><span>Mixed Messages: How climate change is taught in America&#039;s public schools</span>
</h2>
<a href="https://ncse.com/files/MixedMessagesReport.pdf">
<div class="field-field_type_of_study field-label-hidden">
            <div>Read the white paper</div>
      </div>
</a>
<div class="cover"><a href="https://ncse.com/files/MixedMessagesReport.pdf"></a></div>
</div>
<div class="research-right">
    
<div class="field-field_topics field-label-hidden">
      <div>
              <div>Climate change</div>
          </div>
  </div>

<div class="field-field_year field-label-hidden">
            <div>2016</div>
      </div>


<div class="field-field_body">

          <article><p><em><strong>Mixed Messages: How Climate Change is Taught in America's Public Schools</strong></em>&nbsp;is a detailed report of the first nationwide survey of climate change education in the United States, conceived and funded by NCSE and conducted in collaboration with researchers at Pennsylvania State University.</p>
</article>
    
</div>


