      </div>

<h2><span>Dispatches from the evolution wars: shifting tactics and expanding battlefields</span>
</h2>
<a href="https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev-genom-082509-141815">
<div class="field-field_type_of_study field-label-hidden">
            <div>Read the journal article</div>
      </div>
</a>
<div class="cover"><a href="https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev-genom-082509-141815"></a></div>
</div>
<div class="research-right">
    
<div class="field-field_topics field-label-hidden">
      <div>
              <div> Evolution education</div>
              <div> Creationism</div>
          </div>
  </div>

<div class="field-field_year field-label-hidden">
            <div>2010</div>
      </div>


<div class="field-field_body">

          <article><p>To understand the ongoing challenges facing evolution education in the United States, it is necessary to appreciate creationist actions at the different levels of educational governance — state legislatures, state boards of education, local boards of education, and finally the individual classroom — that serve as the battlegrounds for the evolution education wars.</p></article>
    
</div>





</div>

  </div>

  </div>

</div>
    <div class="views-row"><div class="container gray node-type-research">
  <div class="inner"  about="/evolution-and-creationism-americas-classrooms-national-portrait">

<div class="research-left">

<div class="field-field_thumbnail field-label-hidden">
            <div>  <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/partner_logo/public/2019-09/PLOS-Biology_image2.png?itok=jpH4grUM" width="176" height="56" alt="" typeof="foaf:Image" />


</div>
      </div>

<h2><span>Evolution and creationism in America&#039;s classrooms: A national portrait</span>
</h2>
<a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosbiology/article?id=10.1371/journal.pbio.0060124">
<div class="field-field_type_of_study field-label-hidden">
            <div>Read the journal article</div>
      </div>
</a>
<div class="cover"><a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosbiology/article?id=10.1371/journal.pbio.0060124"></a></div>
</div>
<div class="research-right">
    
<div class="field-field_topics field-label-hidden">
      <div>
              <div> Evolution education</div>
          </div>
  </div>

<div class="field-field_year field-label-hidden">
            <div>2008</div>
      </div>


<div class="field-field_body">

          <article><p><em><strong>Evolution and Creationism in America's Classrooms: A National Portrait</strong></em>, the first nationally representative survey of teachers concerning the teaching of evolution, found that a majority teach the topic inaccurately or inadequately.&nbsp;</p></article>
    
</div>


